# .trivyignore — Documented exceptions for CVEs with no available fix.
#
# Policy: entries are added ONLY when ALL of the following are true:
#   1. Fixed Version is absent from the Trivy report (no upstream patch exists)
#   2. The vulnerability has been assessed for exploitability in this context
#   3. A monitoring note is recorded so the entry is revisited when a fix ships
#
# Every entry MUST include: CVE ID, date added, package, reason, and review trigger.
# Remove the entry immediately when a fixed version becomes available in Debian 12.

# ─── CVE-2026-0861 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Package   : libc6 (glibc) 2.36-9+deb12u13
# Severity  : HIGH
# Status    : affected — no fixed version in Debian 12 (bookworm) as of 2026-03-20
# Title     : glibc: Integer overflow in memalign leads to heap corruption
# Reference : https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-0861
#
# Why no patch is possible:
#   Debian upstream has not released a patched libc6 for bookworm. The distroless
#   image (gcr.io/distroless/nodejs24-debian12) bundles the official Debian 12
#   glibc; there is no alternative glibc build available that resolves this CVE.
#   We cannot replace or upgrade glibc within a distroless image.
#
# Exploitability in this context:
#   The vulnerability is an integer overflow in glibc's memalign() triggered by
#   abnormally large alignment values. Exploitation requires an attacker to control
#   memory allocation parameters at the libc level inside the Node.js process.
#   Node.js allocates memory through V8's heap and the OS, not through direct
#   memalign() calls from untrusted input. No known exploit path exists for this
#   CVE through a Node.js HTTP API receiving JSON/form data.
#
# Review trigger:
#   Check https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-0861 weekly.
#   Remove this entry and re-run Trivy as soon as a fixed libc6 version appears
#   in Debian 12 stable or a backport is published.
#
# Added   : 2026-03-20
# Owner   : platform/security
CVE-2026-0861
